I want to help people in need. I want to work with children who have been hurt or ignored. I also want to help families who are having problems. This is why I want to study social work.  I believe in helping others. I believe in treating everyone with respect. I believe in being honest and doing the right thing.

I have always wanted to help people. When I was in school, I saw many people who were hurting. I saw people who did things that were not good for them. I wanted to help, but I did not know how. I got a degree in psychology. I think it will help me understand people better.

One day, I met a boy who was being hurt by his parents. I wanted to help him. I talked to the police. I talked to the boy's parents. I want to help other children like him.

I also believe in fair treatment for everyone. I think everyone should be treated equally. I have always protested against unfairness. I have done things to show that I believe in fairness. I will continue to fight for what is right.

This paper talks about two ways to look at insomnia: the biological way and the sociocultural way. The biological way looks at genes and how body works. The sociocultural way looks at how things like family, money, and culture can affect sleep. This paper will show how studies support each way of looking at insomnia.

Insomnia is a sleep problem.

It can be a problem on its own, or it can be connected to other problems, like mental illness or a medical condition. Some common sleep problems include:

* **Primary Insomnia:** Trouble falling asleep or staying asleep.
* **Primary Hypersomnia:** Trouble staying awake.
* **Narcolepsy:**  Sudden sleep attacks.

The biological way to look at sleep problems focuses on the brain. The part of the brain called the hypothalamus controls sleep. 

One study looked at mice and found that there are special parts of the brain called neurons that control sleep and wakefulness. These neurons have special parts called receptors.  One kind of receptor, the GABAB receptor, helps to make people sleepy.

If the GABAB receptor doesn't work right, people might have trouble sleeping. This shows that genes and how our brains are built can affect sleep.

The sociocultural way to look at sleep problems looks at how our lives affect our sleep. Things like stress, money problems, and family problems can make it hard to sleep.

This paper talks about three things about Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, it says what CAPD is. Next, it talks about how doctors find out if someone has CAPD. Last, it talks about how teachers can help students with CAPD in a normal classroom.

Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) is when the brain does not work well with sound. It means the brain cannot use sound well, even if a person can hear just fine.  People with CAPD hear sounds, but their brain has trouble understanding what they hear. 

People first talked about CAPD in the 1950s. Back then, they called it “auditory imperception”.

CAPD can cause many problems. Some people with CAPD have trouble hearing sounds from different directions. They may have trouble telling sounds apart. They may have trouble understanding words, especially in noisy places. 

To find out if someone has CAPD, doctors do tests. They might ask the person questions. They might watch how the person listens to sounds. There is no one test that can always tell if someone has CAPD.

Doctors do not know why some people have CAPD.

The play Twelfth Night say that disguise good for trick people. But in the end, a person must stop using the new face, or they will lose who they are. It hard to stop a trick because people may be angry. A person must choose: keep their own self, or keep their friends. Some people will not care if they tricked. But others will be sad.

Hiding as a different gender is a big problem. It makes people ask, why? Why hide who they are? Viola hide as a man to be safe. She say, “I’ll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)

Viola hide to protect herself. But this also make her sad because she not with other women. This make things worse because Olivia think Viola is a man and falls in love. Olivia say, “Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.” (5.1.138)

Viola also have feelings for Orsino. He say, “Boy, thou hast said to me a thousand times/ Thou never shouldst love woman like to me.” (5.1. 260-261)

Twelfth Night show how hiding can help people see their true feelings. Olivia and Orsino may have feelings they do not know about. Viola make them see this.

Maybe Olivia like Cesario because he a man. Or maybe Olivia like women. It hard to say. But Olivia may be making fun of people who judge others by how they look. She falls in love with Sebastian easily. She also start to think of Viola as family, not a lover: “A sister, you are she.” (5.1.315)

German rule in Africa was hard.  People say it was bad, especially for the Ovaherero and Nama people in German South West Africa.  There was a big killing of these people. 

But it is not fair to say that all of German rule was bad.  German rule was different in different places. 

The same was true for schools.  When Britain took over German East Africa, they saw many Africans who could read and write.  German schools in other places were good, too. 

But in South West Africa, things were different.  The German government did not give much help to schools for Africans.  Instead, they let missionaries run most of the schools.  The government did help schools for white people. They built schools and gave money to missionary schools.

This made a big difference. While other places had many educated Africans, most Africans in South West Africa could not read or write.

This paper looks at why this happened. It looks at the ideas of white people who lived there and the people who ruled them.


There are many books about schools in German colonies.  Most of these books are old and in German.  They talk about how schools worked.  Later books in English looked at how schools worked in different parts of the German colonies.  One book compares schools in South West Africa and East Africa. This book says that many white people living in South West Africa made the schools different. 

South West Africa was a nice place to live. It was not as hot as some other places. There were a lot of white people there. By 1913, there were nearly 15,000 white people in South West Africa, which was more than any other German colony except East Africa.

Popular music has many kinds of music. It is hard to list them all. Many kinds of music, like rap, rock, country, jazz, and folk, have many smaller kinds. Heavy metal music is one kind that has changed a lot. It is popular and has many different sounds.

Heavy metal music has many feelings, but they are often dark. People have made many different types of heavy metal music.  Some people like fast metal, some like slow metal, and some like metal with singing that is very high or very low.

Because metal music is so different, it is hard to say what it is. It has parts from many other kinds of music. But it started from one place. To understand metal music today, we need to know where it began.

Metal music is dark. It is loud and has strong music. People who play metal music are good at playing their instruments. They play fast and hard.  

Metal music also started when people used drugs. In the 1970s, people used a lot of drugs. This made the music different and new. 

Metal music is also dark because it talks about heavy things. It shows the darker side of life. This was new in music because most music before was happy.


Metal music also has some parts from old music called romantic music. Romantic music was also dark and sad.  

One song that shows this is "Helter Skelter" by The Beatles. It is a very loud and fast song. Some people say it was one of the first heavy metal songs. The Beatles wanted to show that they could be as loud and dark as the Rolling Stones.

Henri Rousseau was a artist. He made art long before other artists made art like his.

Rousseau’s famous painting, “The Dream,” shows a woman in a dream. This is like Rousseau’s own dream. He wanted people to like his art. He wanted to be a good artist.

But Rousseau had a hard time. He did not go to art school. He worked for the government until he was old. He wanted to be liked by other artists, but he also wanted to make his own kind of art.

Rousseau was born in France in 1844. He was poor. He had a hard life. His wife and children died. He started painting to feel better. He wanted to paint like other artists, but he also wanted to be different.

Rousseau’s art was different. He was not like other artists. He did not paint like the famous artists of his time. He wanted to be accepted, but he also wanted to be himself.

His painting “The Dream” shows his struggle. He was a good artist, but he wanted more. He wanted people to like him.

Many people think that good things and beautiful things are connected. This is true. Think about what the writer John Keats said: “Beauty is truth, truth beauty. / That is all / Ye know on earth, and all ye need to know.” 

We learn a lot from school and life. But we know good and bad without being taught. Good things and beautiful things are like this. We try to explain why something is good or beautiful, but we can not say exactly why. We can talk about a picture, like the Mona Lisa, but we can not say why it is good art. When we like something, we say, “There's just something about it.”  We can not explain it.

Stories are like this too. A story can say things that words can not say.  We can talk about a story, but there is still something more. This something is special.

Good things and art are special. They make us feel things deep inside. This feeling can not be explained. Literature is special because it makes us think about good things.

Germany today is a strong country. It has one culture. This culture is seen from the Alps in Munich to the Baltic Sea city of Kiel. The same culture is seen from Cologne on the Rhine River to the city of Dresden on the Elbe River. It is not a surprise that Germany has a unique culture. Germany comes from many different tribes. 

The land where Germany is today is called Germania. Historians do not know for sure where the name comes from. Tacitus said the name came from a Germanic tribe called the Tungrians. They were called Germans before they crossed the Rhine River and fought the Gauls (Tacitus, 98). Julius Caesar first used the word “Germanus” in his book about the Gallic Wars. He fought against the Germans who crossed the Rhine River. He used the word to show the difference between the Gauls he conquered and the Germans he had not conquered. Some people think "Germanus" means neighbor in the Gaulish language. In the first chapter of his book about the Gallic Wars, Caesar wrote: “Germans, who dwell beyond the Rhine, with whom they (The Gauls) are continually waging war.....They contend with the Germans in almost daily battles.” (Julius Caesar, 50-40 BC) Others think the name comes from a spear the Germans used in war, called a ger (O.E.D, 2010), or maybe it comes from the Old Irish word garim, which means “to shout”, because the Germans were loud (Names of Germany).

Tacitus was a Roman historian. He wrote in 98 AD about the origins of the Germans. He said, “I should regard (The Germans) as aboriginal, and not mixed at all with other races through immigration or intercourse. For, in former times it was not by land but on shipboard that those who sought to emigrate would arrive.......Who would leave Asia, or Africa, for Italy for Germany, with its wild country, its inclement skies, its sullen manners and aspect, unless indeed it were his home?(SIC)” (Tacitus, 98) 

Why would Romans go to Germania? They did not go there. They went to Germania to get goods and sometimes fought there. But mostly they went back to their big empire. When the Germanic tribes appeared in the first century, they lived near the Roman Empire. They traded goods and some of them worked in the Roman army (Ozment, 2005 pg. 17).

I look down. My mind see the thing in front of me. I look, but I do not feel. I look with my mind. My thoughts come and go fast. My mind works good. It is like a clear stream. I have no real thoughts, only what I see.
Once, an artist tell me to read a book. The book is called "The New Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain". I want to learn to draw since I was six years old. This book teach you to draw.
The book say to put a box around a picture. This make the picture simple. I look at a bowl of fruit. The book say to see only the bowl of fruit. Not the kitchen, not the table.
I look at the bowl. I am amazed. I see big art. Picasso paint blue things. Monet paint green things. I want to paint brown things. This is my start.
I take a tool. My hand move. I try to make art. I think of water. It is smooth and clear. Things are floating in it. My hand move again. It is hard now. I try to flush the toilet. The brown thing will not go down. I am mad.
I have a mop. I wear a green tie. I look at the brown thing in the toilet. It is gross. I flush again. I think. Then I take toilet paper and wrap it around my hand. I dip my hand in the water. It is like I am putting a turkey in the oven.

Teenagers are having many car accidents. Many things make this a big problem for young drivers. The National Institutes of Health say that young brains are not ready for the dangers of driving. New drivers also do not have much experience. This lack of experience causes more accidents, rollover crashes, speeding, and driving off the road.

Teenagers do worse when they drive with their friends, which they often do. A study in California showed that the younger the passenger, the more likely there is to be an accident.

Some states try to make roads safer by giving young drivers special licenses. These licenses limit when teens can drive and how many young people can be in the car.

But these special licenses are not enough. Young drivers are, on average, not able to handle the risks of driving. Psychologist Marvin Zuckerman thinks 18 is too young to have a regular license. He says young people want to take risks for fun. It makes sense to wait until they are older to drive.

If we do not change the rules, many more teenagers will die. By 2010, many more young people will be old enough to drive. We need to make driving safer for everyone.

There is a simple way to help. Schools can teach teens about driving, but no one under 18 should be allowed to drive. They could get a special permit before getting a license. They should also practice driving with an adult.

Many states already have rules like this. We should have rules like this everywhere in the United States. This will help keep teenagers safe.

I looked at films from the Library of Congress. I watched all the trick films from 1895 to 1901. There were fifteen of them. These films use special editing to show tricks. I looked at most of the films. I wrote about how they were made. I also looked at some later films and saw how they were different.  

Most trick films from this time are made inside. They are like a stage play. The camera stays in one place and does not move. This was common in early films. It came from plays and magic shows.

One problem with this style is that people in the films can only move side to side. They cannot walk toward or away from the camera. For example, look at the film "Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel" (1900). The actors walk back and forth on the stage. They do not come closer to the camera.

These films are also made with long shots. The camera does not zoom in on people. This is like a play where the audience sees everything at once. 

Most trick films are very short. They are usually about one minute long. This is because each trick is one film. The tricks are short, like magic shows.


One important thing to remember is that a trick film can be many shots put together. One trick might look like one shot, but it is actually many shots put together. Look at the film "The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots" (1895). If you look closely, you will see how many shots were used to make the trick with Mary's head.

John Taylor from Carolina was a strong supporter of Republican ideas. He was mainly a farmer, but his work and short time in politics made him known for being strong about people's freedom and how the government worked.  His beliefs about farming shaped his ideas about the government. He wanted to protect and help farming, which made him talk a lot about rules, the Constitution, and even the courts.

Taylor believed the United States had a chance to make a perfect system because there were no old ways to get in the way. This meant they could make a system where people ruled themselves. He strongly believed in people's basic rights and that they were all connected. If one right was taken away, they all were weaker. These rights should be safe from the government. He said what some call "the state of nature" meant strong people and those who were mean would win, but in a civilized society, this should not be true.

To make this good society, Taylor thought the government had to understand the good and bad parts of people. He was very strict about good and bad being separate. He said, "As government is exercised by man, all its virtues and vices must be human" (pg. 167). He thought good rules protected private property, helped farming, and stopped too much capitalism. He believed a good government would work fairly no matter who ran it, because people in charge would always want more power and money. He believed people were always trying to get more for themselves, but that was only bad when it made groups that took advantage of others. A good government was needed to keep people's bad parts in check, and even then, it had to be watched carefully so it didn't become bad. 

Taylor, like many other Republicans, wanted the Constitution followed strictly. He wanted a small federal government, with only the powers clearly stated in the Constitution. He knew a big government was expensive and could become a dictatorship.  But he thought a simple, literal reading was dangerous. Without understanding what the writers intended, it could be easily misused. He thought the Declaration of Independence was the real rule book for the United States because it clearly said the country was made up of independent states, not one nation.

Figure 17 shows a big drop in commuter log entries in the project's third month. This was sad. We do not know why this happened.

Winter came to the college in New England. Fewer people bike or walk. This may explain some of the drop. December is the end of the fall semester. Students are busy with school work and grades. They may not have time for the log. December also has the holidays. Students and staff have a long break. Many do not come to campus.

Classes start again in January. This may explain why there are few logs in January. But February is still low.

New projects often have a lot of energy at first. Then, the energy may go down. To fight this, we had Carpool Challenge Week in March. We wanted to make people excited again. It worked. More people logged their trips.

One challenge is keeping people interested in the project. This is hard because of holidays and breaks at college.

Another challenge is that people like to drive. This is common in our culture. We had to give people reasons to use other ways to get around.

We gave prizes like gift cards. Stores offered these. It would be good to see if bigger prizes would work, like a bicycle, car, or electric car.

We kept the prizes the same. Bigger prizes during the project might have helped. Gift cards were good at first. But if we said, "We will have bicycles in December and a car in January," more people might have joined.

An ETF is like a basket of stocks. It tries to follow the price changes of a group of stocks, like a group of companies in the same industry. It is like a stock fund, but you can buy and sell it on the stock market like a single stock.

ETFs have some good things. They are like a stock fund, which means you own a little bit of many companies. ETFs also let you do things like borrow money to buy more stocks or sell stocks you do not own. This is good for people who want to make more money. ETFs also cost less to own than stock funds.

But ETFs have some bad things, too. You have to pay a fee every time you buy or sell an ETF.  

There are many different types of ETFs. It is good to look at all the choices and see if an ETF is right for you.

This paper looks at an ETF called IHF. We will compare this ETF to the ten biggest companies inside it. We want to know if owning the whole ETF is the same as owning these ten companies by themselves. We will also see if there is a better way to own these ten companies to make more money.

We will look at the ten biggest companies in the ETF. They own 63% of the ETF. We will use this to see how these ten companies work together.

The paper shows that owning just the ten biggest companies makes more money than owning the whole ETF. It also has less risk. But we need to know if this difference is big enough to matter.

To know this, we need to look at how much each company's price changes. We want to see if the changes in the ETF are the same as the changes in these ten companies.

Dream-Land is a good poem by Edgar Allan Poe. In “Dream-Land,” Poe uses the word “Thulé” in lines 6 and 56. A teacher named Mabbott says Poe got the word from Virgil. Virgil used the word for an island north of Britain.  The Greeks thought Thulé was the edge of the world. 

It is true that Virgil used the word, but Poe may have learned it from another writer. Poe liked German writers.  

One writer, Karl J. Arndt, says Poe copied a poem by a German writer named Goethe. The poem is called “The King of Thulé.” It is about a king whose wife dies. The king is very sad. He drinks too much and thinks about his dead wife. He gives away his things, but keeps a special cup. He goes to a cliff, throws the cup in the ocean, and then he dies. 


The king in “The King of Thulé” is sad, just like the speaker in “Dream-Land.” Maybe Poe was thinking about his own sadness when he wrote “Dream-Land.” 

Goethe wrote a famous play called “Faust.” Poe might have read “Faust” because he admired another writer, Alfred Lord Tennyson. Tennyson liked Goethe’s work.


Poe used the word “Thulé” twice in his poems. He used it in “Dream-Land” at the beginning and end of the poem. “The King of Thulé” and “Dream-Land” are similar.

The speaker in “Dream-Land” talks about a dark, lonely place. He sees his dead friends. He sees a world without color. These things are similar to what happens in “The King of Thulé.”

A customer who gets hurt in a store can sometimes get extra money in court. This extra money is called "punitive damages." To get this money, the customer must show that the store worker was mean or did not care about safety.

A judge will likely not end the case quickly for Jennifer Palmer. She says a store manager acted badly. She wants extra money because he knew about a spill but did not clean it up.

There was a spill of applesauce in a store.  An employee told the store manager, Paul Martin, about the spill.  He said he was eating and did not have time to clean it. Another employee told him again, but he said the same thing.

Later, Jennifer Palmer slipped on the spill and hurt her back.  She is suing the store for money because of her injury.

In California, a store can be punished with extra money if it did not care about people's safety. The store must have acted on purpose or been very careless.

Palmer will say Martin should have known the spill was dangerous.  Other people had slipped on spills in the store before. Martin still did not clean it up.

Palmer can also say Martin's actions were very bad. Many people had fallen before, but he did not do anything.

Four years ago, I took a class about Islam at CBC. We talked a lot about if Islam is a bad religion. This is still important today. After 9/11, I saw how the news changed how it showed Islam. At first, it was bad. Now, it is very good. In 2001, we could not have had a president like Barack Obama, who has Muslim family.

The story of Muhammad is interesting. I thought Muhammad forced people to be Muslim. He would take over groups and make them follow his religion. But the story says he was a good man. People came to him on their own to learn.

There are things in the story of Muhammad that are like the story of Jesus. For example, Muhammad made food appear for many people. This makes it seem like Muhammad was a good man who did not need to show off.

I think the story tries to make Muhammad look like Jesus. This is bad because it makes the story of Jesus less important.

The story also has many stories about people joining Islam. But some are from people who heard from other people. This makes the stories seem less true.

What bothers me most is that the story makes Muhammad seem like a good man. But history says he was not always good. I wonder if Muslims know the real story about Muhammad.

Jesus teach about love and peace.  But after he die, people change his words.  Many new ideas come to Christianity.  Now, people want to go back to Jesus's first ideas.  

The world change fast.  Old ways are not as strong.  Many people want new things.  Some people want to keep old ways.  But they are not many.

Christians will start to learn more about Jesus's real words.  They will want to know what he really mean.  This will take a long time.  But in the end, Christianity will go back to its first form.

People will forget the new ideas.  They will only follow Jesus's words.  The church will still be strong.  But it will be more like it was when Jesus live.  Everyone will believe the same things.

This is how it will be:  The world change a lot.  History go in circles.  Just like the Roman Empire became Christian, Christianity will go back to its first form.  

To make this happen, people will see Jesus's words in a new way. They will see them as stories, not just facts.  

Before Jesus, there was Judaism.  Judaism was the beginning of Christianity.  They believe in one God.  They believe in the Bible.  They had many groups.  But they all believe in the same God.

"The Jungle" shows that people can be very selfish. They want to make their lives good but do not care about people who are less fortunate. The book shows this in many ways. 

The factory owners and managers are very greedy. They only want to make their companies big and powerful. They do not care about people or the environment. Upton Sinclair writes, "The line of the buildings stood clear-cut and black against the sky; here and there out of the mass rose the great chimneys, with the river of smoke streaming away to the end of the world." He wants to show how much damage pollution does. The owners do not care about people or animals who are hurt by it.

The owners also do not care about their workers. They want to save money and make more profit. They make the workers work long hours and then fire them without warning. They do not give them any help. There were not many laws to protect workers at that time, so the owners could treat them badly. They forced workers to work fast and in unsafe conditions. The book does not say it directly, but it seems like the people who worked in Packingtown were expected to live with these bad conditions. There were no groups to help the workers. 

Some unions existed, but they often took money from the workers. The workers were treated so badly that they felt like slaves. Sinclair writes, "Here is a population, low-class and mostly foreign, hanging always on the verge of starvation and dependent for its opportunities of life upon the whim of men every bit as brutal and unscrupulous as the old-time slave drivers; under such circumstances, immorality is exactly as inevitable, and as prevalent, as it is under the system of chattel slavery."

Many writers use different ways to make readers feel a certain way about important topics. Some ways are better than others. F. Scott Fitzgerald uses many ways to do this in his book *The Great Gatsby*. Sometimes, he uses words that do not usually go together. This makes readers think of something special. Other times, he gives a symbol a meaning and uses it to make readers feel a certain way. 

Fitzgerald does this with colors, like gold, green, white, gray, and red and pink. In his book, he gives these colors special meanings and then uses them to make readers feel a certain way about important things.

Fitzgerald uses white and gray to show sameness. White is a bit nicer and more fancy, while gray is old and faded. He shows this at the start of the book by having people wear white all the time. Daisy and Jordan are always in white. Nick wears white clothes to Gatsby’s party. Tom wears a white shirt when he meets Myrtle. Even Catherine is white. The only time people are not in white is when Nick is seeing Gatsby’s party. The party has bright colors. Fitzgerald also uses white and gray for ordinary things. Nick goes to work down a white street. People at Gatsby’s party have gray names on Nick’s list. Catherine’s apartment is like a white building. He also describes ordinary people and places as white or gray. Jordan and Daisy had a white childhood. There are gray cars and gray land.

After Fitzgerald shows readers white and gray mean sameness, he uses them for important things. He does this with Daisy. After a long time without using these colors, he describes Daisy in white. Readers start to see Daisy as less important, like something Gatsby wants. Fitzgerald does this more with Daisy to make her seem less important. She has a gray fur collar. She is in a white dress before Tom and Gatsby meet.

San Diego has good farms. The weather is good for many crops. Farmers grow tomatoes, oranges, leafy greens, squash, broccoli, herbs, peaches, lemons, berries, honey, and peppers.  Many people in San Diego like food from farms that do not use chemicals. There are many groups that help these farms. They have long waiting lists. People like organic eggs and milk too. Many organic farms let people visit. They can see how the farm works. They can also go hiking or look at birds. This is good for the farmer. It helps them make money and teach people.

Organic farms are good for animals and plants. They do not use chemicals. This helps make more kinds of plants and animals. But organic farms cost more to run. They need more people to work. They also need more care to keep pests away and to feed the soil.  Sometimes organic farms lose more food than farms that use chemicals. Smaller farms do not have as many workers as big farms. Some things that help animals also cost more. This includes planting special plants, moving animals to different areas, removing bad plants, and taking care of plants so they grow in the right way.

A good place for a farm is near the town of Potrero in San Diego. It is 160 acres of bushes, grass, and trees. It is next to a big forest. This area has many plants and animals. Some are in danger of disappearing, like the kangaroo rat, the yellow-legged frog, and some butterflies.

People lived on this land a long time ago. They raised cows and cut wood. This land was given to a person to farm a long time ago. 

I looked at land for sale online and found programs that help farmers. I wanted to see how a small farmer could make money and keep the land good for animals. I also found an organic farm nearby and looked at how it works.

Culture is very important in talking to get things done with other people. Culture is not one thing. It is not the same for everyone. It is not good to say all people from one place are the same.  

To talk to people from another culture, you must try to understand their ways. You can learn about their history and how they feel. You should not judge or try to change their ways. You should accept them. In talks, you must follow their rules. If you are not from the same place, you must be respectful of their way of life. This will help you talk better.

Culture is not just about countries. Companies also have their own cultures. Some companies work long hours. Others are more relaxed. You can see the culture in how people dress, how they talk, and how they hire new people. Some companies like to help people. Others only help certain people.

Even in America, there are many different company cultures. You can see this in different parts of the country. Some cultures are very different from each other. You must look deeper to understand them.

Values are very important because they tell you why people act a certain way. If people value saving face, they will not be embarrassed in front of others. If people value hard work, they will not give up easily. You must understand these things before you talk to people. 

It is also good to learn about the other person. This will help you talk to them better.

The story is about a very smart person, a fool. The fool says, “There is no God.” This story is in a book called the Bible. A man named St. Anselm used this story to talk about God. Another man, St. Thomas Aquinas, also talked about God. Both men believed in God.

We will look at their ideas. They both believe in the same God. So, we will compare their ideas. We must think that they both believe in God.  We can’t compare their ideas if we don’t.

Each man has good points. But neither man gives us a complete reason to believe in God.

First, let’s look at St. Anselm. He said that we can know God by thinking about Him. He said that God exists in our minds. We know God is real because we can think about Him. We don’t need to look outside ourselves to find proof. This is called faith.

This is different from what St. Thomas Aquinas said. He said we can know God by using our minds and by looking at things around us. We don’t need faith. We can see God in the world.  

St. Thomas gave five reasons why God must exist. He said that everything changes, so there must be something that does not change. He said that everything is caused by something else, so there must be a first cause. He said that not everything can be eternal, so there must be something eternal. He said that there are different levels of goodness, so there must be a perfect being. He said that the world is ordered and harmonious, so there must be a designer.

Many years ago, in the fifth or sixth century before Christ, a prince was born. He would one day be called Buddha. Buddha gave up his life of riches and became wise. His ideas started the religion of Buddhism. The most important part of Buddhism is called Theravada. Buddhism is very old, about two thousand five hundred years. Today, it is different from when Buddha lived.

We can see this in Sri Lanka, a country where many Theravada Buddhists live. There is a yearly ceremony called the water-cutting ceremony. Monks and regular people take part. This ceremony is important to them, even though Buddha never talked about it. These differences are all over, from small things to the most important ideas of Buddhism.

The people who follow Theravada Buddhism, both monks and regular people, have changed how they think about religion over time. This has happened because of things both inside and outside Buddhism, some good and some bad.

We will talk about some words a lot.

Inside forces come from people who follow Buddhism, whether they are monks or not. Outside forces come from people who do not follow Buddhism.

A bad force is something that hurts Buddhism or wants to hurt it. A good force does not want to hurt or help Buddhism, but it might do one or the other by accident.

First, we need to talk about the basic ideas of Theravada Buddhism. Buddhists find safety in three things: the Buddha, the Dhamma, and the Sangha. The Dhamma is all the writings of Buddhism.

They are called the Tripitaka, which means the three baskets. The Sutta Pitaka has stories about Buddha. The Vinaya Pitaka has rules for monks. The Abhidhamma Pitaka talks about the deep ideas of Buddhism. These ideas are about things like Anatta, which means there is no soul, Dukkha, which means life has suffering, and Anicca, which means everything changes. If you understand these ideas, you can end Sansara, which is the endless cycle of death and rebirth.

Along with Sansara will end lobha, which is wanting things, dosa, which is anger, and moha, which is being confused. These end when you become enlightened. The Vinaya Pitaka has rules for how to live. Regular people have five rules: do not kill, do not lie, do not steal, do not have sex with the wrong people, and do not drink alcohol.

Monks have many more rules. The most important idea in Buddhism is the four noble truths. First, life has suffering. Second, wanting things causes suffering. Third, suffering can end. And fourth, there is a way to end suffering.

The United States and Mexico had a big fight for many years. This fight went on for fifty-seven years, from eighteen thirty-six to eighteen ninety-three. (Diehl and Goerts 2000 p. 145). The biggest fight was the Mexican-American War of eighteen forty-six to eighteen forty-eight. The United States beat Mexico and took Texas and the American Southwest. There were many other fights between the two countries. They finally stopped fighting right before World War One. 

The fight started because Americans and Mexicans had different ideas about religion, culture, and how to live. They also wanted the same things. This is like many other countries that fight. Countries that live next to each other often have problems. The United States and Mexico are like this. David M. Pletcher (1977) says, “Only in Mexico and Cuba can one find long-lasting problems with the United States” (p. 41). Mexico and Cuba are close to the United States and have fought with it. Other countries in Latin America have good relations with the United States. 

Religion was a big problem between the two countries.  This has happened to many countries in history. Sally Frahm (2001) says that “if in the twentieth century Americans were against fascism and communism, in the eighteenth and nineteenth they were against Catholicism and monarchy” (p.86).  It was like the Cold War between the United States and the Soviet Union. There was an idea fight and a fight over what each country wanted. But this time, it was not about politics but about religion. 

Americans and Mexicans did not trust each other because their old rulers did not trust each other. This made it hard for them to be friends. Diehl and Goerts (2000) say there were seventeen fights between Mexico and the United States in fifty-seven years. Most of these fights were over land. Bandits and bad people from American towns would go into Mexico and cause trouble. This was a big problem until both countries sent soldiers to their borders (Schmitt 1974 p. 97).

Schmitt (1974) says the fight started to end when Mexico needed the United States a lot. The fight finally ended when the United States wanted to control Mexico’s money instead of taking its land. This happened at the end of the nineteenth century (p.110).

Fifteen years ago, I got very sick. I did not know I was sick. I was a nurse. I chose this job because I wanted to be safe.  When I was young, people told me, "You can always find work. People always get sick." So, I became a nurse.

I wanted to be a scientist or a journalist, but I did not. I was 46 years old and single. I had no money. I could not work. I am still sick. I live on government help. I have nothing. Every day is hard. I am not safe. I feel bad about myself.

My family and friends help me. I could not live without them. When bad things happen, you need help.

There are always problems in life. We cannot plan for everything. Sometimes, we need help from others.

I agree that we should not rely only on the government. It is not working well. But we should help each other.

People say that the US was built by strong, independent people. But people helped each other. They shared things. The people who traveled west in covered wagons helped each other.

Be prepared for problems. I am. I have food, water, and tools. I also know my neighbors.

Why do living things change over time? Are there limits to how they change?  Even today, we do not fully understand how to describe the shapes of living things with math.  

Scientists have used math to study how shells change over time. This study looks at how math and experiments can help us understand how changes happen in the shells of a type of sea snail called *Prunum*.

We used X-rays to measure the shape of *Prunum* shells. We used special computer programs to make models of different shell shapes. These models help us see the limits of how *Prunum* shells can change.

We are combining these models with experiments to understand how shells change over long periods of time.

A shell is like a tube that turns as it grows.  The turns are called whorls.  Each whorl has a line separating it from the next whorl. This line is called a suture. The biggest whorl is the last one, called the body whorl.  The rest of the whorls are called the spire. The very tip of the spire is called the apex, and the opposite end is called the base.  The animal lives inside the shell and comes out through an opening called the aperture.

Scientists look at shells from different angles.  The most common view is the apertural view, where the opening is facing the viewer.

To count the whorls, look at the shell from the top (apical view). Find the first suture line and draw a line across the shell. Count the whorls from that line, guessing to the nearest quarter of a whorl.

A shell is a series of openings that change over time as the animal grows. We can track the path of these openings using math.

By using math, we can understand how shells are made and how they change.

Indonesia has had few changes in baby and child deaths in the last ten years.  The country is close to reaching many of the Millennium Development Goals, like clean water and toilets. But, the rate of progress for mothers and children's health is not fast enough to reach the goals for 2015. This text talks about the reasons for these problems. It says that Indonesia needs to make its health system better, rather than just focusing on special programs. 

Indonesia has made progress in the number of births with a worker who knows about health. Now 72% of births have this. But, this number includes helpers like midwives who cannot give medical help when a pregnancy is hard. So, the progress is not as good as it seems. Also, fewer children under five with diarrhea are seeing a doctor. We do not have all the information about care after birth, but it is clear this is a problem too.

C-sections are not common, only 4% of the time. This shows another problem. In cities, 7% of births are c-sections, but only 2% in the countryside. This means people in cities have better access to healthcare. There is also a big difference in how well different groups of people can get healthcare. The poorest people are 27% less likely to use healthcare than the richest. This is likely because they cannot afford it.

To improve health for mothers and babies, we need to think about how to get people better healthcare. Should Indonesia focus on special programs, or make the whole health system better?

Programs are easier to manage and show quick results. But, they can take money away from other health areas.  Also, many programs can do the same thing, wasting time and money.

Victorian books are known for showing a lot of detail and focusing on rich people from that time. But there are two books, "Oliver Twist" and "Wuthering Heights," that are from that time but are different. Both books have mystery and strange things that happen, which is not typical of books from that time. This helps make the characters stronger and gives us a better understanding of why they act the way they do.

One example is from "Oliver Twist":

“And now, many confusing thoughts came to his mind. He felt like he was still with Sikes and Crackit, who were arguing loudly. He could hear their words. When he paid attention to himself, he found that he was talking to them. Suddenly, he jumped back at the sound of gunshots. Loud cries and shouts filled the air. Lights flashed before his eyes, and everything was loud and chaotic, as if an unseen hand was quickly taking him away. 

Through all these quick images, there was a feeling of pain that he couldn't get rid of. It bothered him all the time.”

(Dickens, 220)

These books often use dreams or dreamlike states to create mystery. In "Oliver Twist," these strange events often show us more about Oliver’s feelings and what is troubling him. When Oliver is shot, he remembers it vividly in chapter 28, as if he is dreaming. He is trying to find help. This shows how little control Oliver has over what happens to him. He is hurt badly and is in a lot of pain. He doesn't even notice the "unseen hand" that takes him away. He is overwhelmed with despair. The shooting happens again, but without the shock of the pain. The pain is now constant and linked with fear, not surprise.

The shooting makes us wonder whose fault it is that Oliver is in this situation. It's certainly not his fault. This shows that Oliver has little control over anything. Even when his life is in danger, he can't try to change things. This makes us think that Oliver is starting to give up. It seems like Fagin has broken him and made him accept this despair. Otherwise, we can assume that Oliver would have tried to do something, even just to save himself.



“The day passed.  Day? There was no day; it was gone as soon as it came – and night came on again; night so long, and yet so short; long in its dreadful silence and short in its fleeting hours.”

A few years ago, I worked in an after school program. I helped young students with their school work. I was good at helping them with English and reading.

A teacher asked me to help a boy named Adrian. He was in third or fourth grade. Adrian had trouble reading. It was very strange. He could read some letters, but not others. It was confusing. 

I knew Adrian was from a Latino family. He spoke English very well. We worked hard, but things were not getting better. Then, one day, Adrian's mother came to the program. She only spoke Spanish. I didn't speak much Spanish, but we found ways to talk. 

That is when I realized something. Adrian could read, but he did not know the English alphabet well.  

I don't know if this helped Adrian much, but I hope he is doing better now.

I told this story to talk about the problem of language barriers in schools, especially in California. It is not always easy to see the problem. Even children who speak English well can have trouble.  

We all agree that this is a problem. So what can we do? For Adrian, the answer was simple: help him learn English reading and how to pronounce the letters. But for children who do not speak much English, the answer is more difficult. There is no one right way to help them.

One good idea is to use a dual language system. This is good for all children, not just those whose first language is Spanish. Studies show that children who learn two languages do better in school. Some people are afraid of this idea. They say it is a waste of money and that most children will not benefit. This is not true. If we used this system in all classrooms, all children would benefit.

How can we do this? We do not need to make all teachers bilingual. That is too hard. But we could have special helpers who speak two languages.

From we small we hear stories about big things.  Big things we can not understand. Some people go to church or temple to learn about these big things. Some people think about these big things alone. Many people believe the things they learn from their parents. Some people do not believe. They think the world is all they know. We all want to know who we are. We look for answers. We want to find light in the dark.

One day I asked my father what bird he liked best. We sat on the porch. Rain fell on the roof. We smoked. The rain made the plants on the porch wet. My father looked at the rain. He looked far away. He was thin now. His hair was thin too. He did not look at me. I felt sad. I wanted to say I loved him, but I was afraid to say it. I hugged him. We sat in silence, watching the rain.

My father died in December. He died five days after my birthday. The medicine made him live longer, but it did not make him happy. I did not know why God would let him suffer. I did not pray. I thought God had stopped listening to me.

I did not want to watch him die. I did not want to see him leave the world. I wanted to remember him as he was, not how he died. I knew him better than anyone else. He would not want me to watch him die. I stayed in bed for three days. No one called me.

The "Gothic Novel" is strange. It is old and new at the same time. This is what Ian Watt says in his book "The Rise of the Gothic Novel."  People have said lots of things about the Gothic style. Some say it is not good. Others say it is great. Some say it is not deep. Others say it is very powerful. The first Gothic novel, "The Castle of Otranto" by Horace Walpole, used old ideas from stories and new ideas from modern novels to make a new kind of story. Walpole used old ways of telling stories on stage and new ways of describing nature to make his story. He calls it "A Gothic Story."  The Gothic style uses old ideas from medieval stories and buildings. Even when "The Castle of Otranto" was first published, the word "Gothic" was used for many things. It meant old and not modern. But the way stories were told in Gothic novels was new. It let readers see inside the minds of the characters. That is why Gothic stories are still popular today.

One big idea in Gothic novels is "Chivalry." Chivalry is the way knights were trained to be brave and honorable. This idea is important in "The Castle of Otranto." Gothic writers liked chivalry because it showed what a knight should be like. They wanted to show that people today were not like that. Walpole wrote "The Castle of Otranto" during a time when things were very political. He was worried about the future. He may have thought that people were not as good as knights from the past.  This idea is shown in a character named Frederic. The reader knows that Frederic is a good person. He is a prince who has suffered and is brave. He is described like this:


The description of Frederic shows many things about knights. He is a prince. He has been through sadness. He is supposed to be dead. The description makes him seem like a very good knight, maybe even too good. This is a common idea in Gothic stories.

Supply chain management is how goods move. It starts when a customer wants something. Then, it goes from making raw materials, to making the product, and finally to the customer.  The idea of supply chain management started in 1982. A man named Keith Oliver came up with the name. He said it is about planning, doing, and checking everything in the process so customers get what they want quickly and well.  

There are six important parts to supply chain management: making the product, getting the parts, storing the goods, picking a good place for the work, moving things around, and sharing information.  Managers use these parts to make customers happy.

Making the product is the first step. It is the base of the whole process. Managers need to know what customers want. They look at the market to see what people want to buy. Once they know what people want, they decide what to make and how much. They also decide where to make it. They need to pick a place that can make the goods well and quickly. 

After that, they plan how much work needs to be done and how to keep the machines working. Making the product is very important. Every detail matters. If a manager does not plan well, it can cost a lot of time and money.

The next part is getting the parts. A company might make parts in many different places. Each place might have different workers and machines. Managers need to choose the best place for each part. Sometimes, companies give some of the work to other companies. This is called outsourcing. Companies do this to make things faster and cheaper.

Hitler is alive in Burma, the sign says.

Ellen Page, star of Juno, is alone on a street. She holds a piece of cardboard. On it, a message is written with a marker. Burma, also called Myanmar, is a country in Southeast Asia. It is ruled by a group of soldiers. In 1962, they took over the government. In 2007, people protested in the streets. These were the first protests in ten years. Many monks led the protests. They are called "The Saffron Revolution" because the monks wear yellow robes.

At first, the government let the monks hold peaceful meetings. But then, things became violent. The army attacked the monks. They went into the monasteries and destroyed them. The army arrested many foreign reporters. One reporter, Kenji Nagai from Japan, was killed on September 27, 2007. He was just watching a protest. The government says 13 people died. But a soldier who left the army said many more people died.

This is not new. Governments have always tried to stop people from protesting.  Roman emperors said they were chosen by God to rule. Japanese emperors are thought to be gods. Our president, George W. Bush, talks to Ted Haggard, the leader of a group called "Stupid People Worldwide".

There have been many bad things that have happened because of this. In 1989, people protested in Tiananmen Square in China. Soldiers killed many people. The Chinese government says 200-300 died. But other groups say thousands died. In Rwanda in the 1990s, people were killed because of their religion. Hitler killed many Jews in Europe.

Duke Ellington was a good jazz musician. He played music for a long time. He was good at making music with his band. Ellington played the piano, but he was better at writing music. His music was complex and good. He wrote music that showed off each band member's skill. Ellington made rules for the music so soloists could play freely. He also wrote music that sounded good together.

A book about music, called The Grove Music Dictionary, said Ellington used voice as a musical tool. His song "Creole Love Call" shows this. He used voice to make the music sound different. 

"Creole Love Call" is slow and sad. It has six parts. The first part has voice and wind instruments talking back and forth. The voice sounds smooth at first, but then rougher. The second part has a trumpet playing a slow solo. The third part has a clarinet playing high notes. The fourth part has the whole band playing like the first part. The fifth part is the loudest. The wind instruments play high notes, and the brass and drums play a special beat. The sixth part is like the first part. The voice sounds rough and plays like an instrument. The song ends with a special sound from the trumpet.

Ellington used voice like an instrument in many songs. In "Hot and Bothered," he had a trumpet player named "Bubber" Miley and a singer named Baby Cox talk back and forth. The trumpet sounded like singing, and the singing sounded like playing an instrument.

In "It Don't Mean a Thing (If It Ain't Got That Swing)," Ellington used a trombone player named Joe "Tricky Sam" Nanton. Nanton played the first part of the song on the trombone.

She always want some thing. This want was strong. It start when she was about fourteen, a young teen.  It still was there three years later, when she was seventeen. By then, she want a person, not a thing. But she did not like any boys. Some boys like her. They try to be nice, but no one was good. She ask herself why. This was strange. Many ideas came to her mind, but nothing good. So she live her life, always asking why.



A day at home was quiet. Her parents were good and calm. They never fight. They did not fight with her much either. The only time they fight was when she act like she was in charge. She was the daughter of calm people, but she was fun and strong. People like her.

Today was not quiet. She walk from room to room, trying to find a new idea. She hear a short cry from the kitchen. It was her mother's voice. She ran to the kitchen, worried. "Mom! Mom, what is wrong?" Her mother was on the floor, hurting. She say "Ow" over and over. Her daughter run to her and put her hand on her. "Ouch... sweet -  ty, I ... need to go to the hospital." Her words were fast. Her daughter knew she was in big pain. "Okay, Mom. Where should I take you?" Her mother pointed.  The daughter was happy she took classes to be strong. She carry her mother to the car, put her in the back, and drive.

The hospital smelled like medicine and sickness. But she did not care. She was busy helping her mother. She take her inside and call for a doctor. Some people came over. Someone got a bed and put her mother on it. They took her away. Her daughter waited, worried.

Her mother fell from a stool. She try to get a vase from a high shelf.

This study looked at if eating a "Mediterranean Diet" (Med diet) helps women avoid heart problems and strokes. The study used a score called "aMed" to measure how well people follow the Med diet. The aMed diet has lots of plants, like fruits, nuts, and beans. It also has fish and good fats.

Scientists knew that eating the Med diet was good for the heart. But they wanted to see if it helped avoid strokes. 

They studied 74,886 women who were nurses.  The women answered questions about what they ate over many years. The scientists looked at medical records to see if these women had heart problems or strokes.

The study found that women who ate more like the aMed diet had less chance of getting heart problems or strokes.

In two thousand seven, the United States had a big money problem.  Many people lost jobs.  Houses lost value. Many big companies had big problems. This problem is still here today. We must ask: how did this happen? How can we stop it?  The problem was made by bad choices.  People in charge made banks give out bad loans. The banks gave these loans to people who could not pay them back.

A company called Fannie Mae and another called Freddie Mac helped make the problem worse. They took these bad loans and sold them to other people. When people could not pay back the loans, Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac lost a lot of money. The problem then spread to other parts of the country.

The problem started in nineteen ninety nine. President Clinton wanted to be president again. He wanted people to like him. So, he made it easier for banks to give out loans. This made the problem worse.

Many new kinds of loans were given out.  These loans were very complex. They were hard to understand.

Many people borrowed a lot of money to buy houses. They thought the prices would go up. But the prices went down. People could not pay back their loans. This made the problem even worse.

Many banks lost a lot of money. Some banks closed. The government had to help.

Ah, exposition. That part in your story where you show off your writing skills.  Or the part where your readers get bored and stop reading.  Dr. Merlin has been known to scream at her computer when she gets stuck in Too Much Information, and not in a good way.

Exposition is not your friend.

You already know the basic writing tip, "Show, don't tell." But Dr. Merlin still writes long passages where nothing happens, or too much. Exposition is like a little devil whispering in your ear, telling you to get the boring stuff out of the way so you can get to the good parts (not to be confused with the other devil whispering that you should tell your audience every detail about every character's childhood).

Exposition is when you tell the reader what happened, usually in simple sentences. In movies, exposition happens when one character tells another a bunch of information, like in "The Rime of the Ancient Mariner." In stories, the author does the telling.

Here's an example.  Imagine you are reading a story, and you're told that the hero met his love at a certain place and time. They got married in a fancy ceremony, and then he was murdered right in front of her. You wouldn't want this whole sequence to take up two pages, with the hero and heroine only getting two lines of dialogue each.

You'd expect the author to spend some time showing you what kind of person the husband was. Maybe his speech and actions show how much he loved his wife. You'd also expect the heroine to show how much he changed her life for the better (especially if the story later tells you that's the case).

A good introduction to the husband's character would help you care about what happens to him. It would also give you insight into the heroine's character: what she saw in him, how close they were, clues about her thoughts and dreams as seen through his eyes, and so on. You would feel sad when he died, and that would make you more connected to the heroine.

In short, you would expect more than just the bare bones of the story: "They met, they married, he died."

As a writer, you need to give the reader the details. Sometimes it's tempting to rush past things.  Maybe you're introducing a new character who used to be in the Air Force, now works the night shift at a gas station, has been married twice, has no kids, loves to fish, secretly wants to own the station someday, and had Eggs Benedict for breakfast.

I watch two news stories from Columbus, Ohio. The first was on NBC 4 this morning (August 13, 2011). The big story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio. He hurt his wife. They did not say her name, but his name was Shad Hostettler. They showed his picture. He looked bad. They talked about this story for about two minutes. They said he hurt his wife many times and was now arrested. 

The next story was about Travis Buyers. He was 18 years old. He was shot in Sharon Woods. He was very hurt. No one was arrested. The police were looking for the person who did it. This story was short. I think it was short because he was a black man. I have seen this before. When a white person is hurt, the news talks a lot about it. But when a black person is hurt, they do not talk about it much.

Next, they talked about a hole in a helicopter. Someone shot at it. It was a small bullet. Crime-Stoppers will give five thousand dollars for help finding the person who shot it.

Then they talked about the rain. It would rain on Saturday. It would be hot.

They also talked about a robbery at a store. A black man robbed it. He wore a hoodie. He was tall and thin. They talked a lot about him being black.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez. He sold drugs. He was in prison for 25 years. They said 300 months. That is a long time.  They also said he was Hispanic. I do not know why they said that.

Brothers have a strong bond. It is a bond that cannot be broken. This bond can bring many feelings: love, pride, jealousy, and anger. Brothers know each other better than anyone else. They see themselves when they look at their brother.

This bond is strong, good or bad, in difficult times. When these feelings are clear, they have a high cost. To understand the feelings between brothers, we must look at the results.  When a brother looks at another brother, he sees his own reflection. He sees himself, not how others see him, but how he really is. His actions and their results show his true character.

The story "The Scarlet Ibis" shows this theme. Two brothers go on a journey in a beautiful place. There is sadness and pride in the end. Only one brother lives.

The story shows us how the main character feels. It shows us how he feels about his little brother, Doodle. The story also shows us how he sees the world. These things influence his choices.

The main character feels strong pride. From the time he and Doodle go out together to the end, he feels angry at Doodle. He wanted a brother he could teach things to, like running, jumping, and climbing. He wanted someone to play with. But Doodle is sick. He cannot do these things. This makes the main character sad. He even thinks about killing Doodle. But Doodle smiles at him, and the main character feels love for him.

The brain is hard to understand. It is like a computer. But it is more than that.

People have tried to explain the brain for a long time. First, they said it was like a tablet. Then they said it was like a book. Now they say it is like a computer.

The brain takes in information from the world. It sees colors, sounds, and feels things. The brain changes this information into signals.

The brain works in two ways. It looks at small parts of information first. Then it uses what it knows to understand the whole thing.

For example, if you see a box, your brain sees the color, shape, and edges. Then it knows it is a box.

The brain also pays attention to what is important. It can choose to focus on one thing and ignore others.

To remember things, the brain stores them in different ways. Some memories are short, like when you are thinking about something. Other memories are long, like your name.

People think the brain stores knowledge in a special way. They are still trying to figure out how it works.

Aldous Huxley shows us a bad future. Technology and money control people. This is in his book, Brave New World. People in this book like to be together and happy. They do not think about themselves.

A leader controls everything. People are not free. They believe what the leader wants them to believe. This is like what Karl Marx talked about. Marx wrote about how money control people.

The book shows how money can make people forget the truth. People only care about getting more things. They do not think about how things are made. This is how money makes people forget the truth, according to Marx.

The people in the book are controlled by the leader. The leader is like a boss in a factory. The leader tells the workers what to do.

People in the book do not have real friendships. They do not have strong feelings. They are just happy to have things. They do not care about each other. This is because money controls them.

I go to University Park. I have been a student here for about two and a half years. I live in a dorm. Many students, like me, have a problem getting around. My dorm is far from most classes. In my first year, I lived in East Halls. This is far from the center of campus. It takes twenty-five minutes to walk to Willard building, near the center. It takes even longer if it rains.  East Halls used to be far from other parts of campus. There was a lot of empty space. Now there are many new buildings and sports fields. As the campus grows, it is harder to get around. What is the best way to get around? A bicycle is good. But the bike is not enough. Students must use the bike, and the campus must be good for bicyclists.

I talked to a friend about this. He rides a bike again after being away from it for a few years. He said bikes are great. It is the best way to get around. Bikes are good for your health and fast. You can go a long way with some food and exercise. I live off campus now. It is as far from the center as some dorms. The best thing I did this year was buy a bike. I have class in Thomas building. It is a long walk from my home. On a bike, it takes five minutes. The road is not always good for bikes.


Walking is good too, but I am too busy. Without a bike, walking is my only choice. Walking to Thomas every day would take thirty to forty minutes extra. That is more than two and a half hours each week. That is too much time.

In pursuing an education in social work, I intend to follow a career path with the Division of Family and Children Services to help children who have been abused or neglected; and to provide support for troubled families. Values that I can provide to the social work field include the following: service, respect, ethical nature, commitment to help improve relationships between others and to improve myself professionally to remain competent in my field. These core values are not just important to social workers; they are important to me personally. 

	I have always wanted to help others, but I was unsure of the career path that I wanted to follow. Throughout my years in high school and college, I saw many individuals flee from their problems in denial and a few used coping mechanisms that were less than ideal. Because of situations that I have witnessed, I chose to pursue a Bachelor’s degree in Psychology. Still unsure of a career path, I decided to take a break once I graduated from Piedmont College in 2009. One day that summer, I visited a friend who introduced me to a sixteen year-old boy sitting nervously on her couch. She explained to me why he was visiting: to escape his abusive parents. The next day, I learned that he had called the police to his parent’s residence. To see if I could help in any way, I drove over to his parents’ house. Once there, I privately explained my concerns to the police and told them I had just graduated with a degree in Psychology from Piedmont College. The police requested that I talk to the parents since there was nothing that the law could do for the teenager. When I questioned the parents about the situation, they seemed nervous and used excuses to describe their son’s “manipulative” behavior for involving outside sources to resolve “simple” disputes. After this particular experience, I began to seriously consider a career in social work to help children with “simple” disputes among family members.

	Another value that is important for the field of social work is social justice. As a society, we claim that the individual is important and we mourn those that we have lost. The concept of the “individual” that society holds is more a follower of archaic traditions than actual uniqueness. So, if society mourns lost individuals, then why do we strive to be similar to “everyone else?” I am an individual and do not enjoy placing limitations on myself to be similar to others. Throughout my years at high school and college, I protested against social injustice whenever I could: coloring my hair unnatural colors, wearing clothing that fit my personality, piercing my ears past the traditional set, declaring my involvement with GSBA (Gay Straight Bisexual Alliance), fighting against both racism and discrimination whenever I witnessed it, etc. I believe in social justice and I will continue to protest against social injustice.

The following paper addresses the Biological and Sociocultural models in relation to the disorder insomnia. The biological model focuses on genetic information that is inherited as well as medical aspects of health. The Sociocultural models look at environmental relationships and their applications to race, ethnicity, demographics, and socioeconomic status. The following review of insomnia looks at these models and explains each piece of research chosen to relate to and to better explain the models. The explanations of the research and their findings are then critiqued to mention their specific strengths and weaknesses.

A sleep disorder can be characterized as a primary sleep disorder, a sleep disorder related to another mental disorder, or a sleep disorder related to other issues. The Primary sleep disorders are Dyssonmias or Parasomnias while sleep disorders related to another mental disorder are related to an Axis I or Axis II disorder. Other categories of sleep disorders can be due to medical complications or the intake of a substance. The Dyssomnias are: Primary Insomnia, Primary Hypersomnia, Narcolepsy, Breathing- Related Sleep Disorder, Circadian Rhythm Sleep Disorder, and Dyssomnia Not Otherwise Specified (NOS). While Primary Insomnia is a complication in adequate or maintained sleep, Primary Hypersomnia is a difficulty in staying awake, both for at least a one month period of time. Narcolepsy involves cataplexy and/ or automatic REM. While Dyssonmias focus on initiating and remaining asleep, the Parasomnias are sleep disorders associated with behavioral abnormalities and/ or physiological occurrences. Parasomnias are Nightmare Disorder, Sleep Terror Disorder, Sleepwalking Disorder, and Parasomnias Not Otherwise Specified. The sleep disorders related to another mental disorder involve sleep difficulties due to Axis I (Clinical Disorders) or Axis II (Personality Disorders or Mental Retardation). The following review focuses on insomnia, and somewhat on primary sleep disorders in general in relation to the biological and sociocultural models.

	 The biological model of sleep disorders focuses on genes, heritable factors, and physiologically acquired aspect of sleep disorders. Neurons in the hypothalamus containing orexin are responsible for the regulation of sleep and wakefulness. This study experimented with mice and found that there are phenotypic GABAB receptors on the orexin neurons which are specifically responsible for sleep/ wake states. The activation of the GABAA receptor induces responses that promote sleep. If it is inhibited from firing, this can cause reduced anxiety and induce sleep. The GABAB agonist (baclofen) increased sleep time (Matsuki et al., 2009). Such results imply that the animal models of mice can be generalized to studies in humans. This shows that there is a genetic and environmental basis for the physical GABAB receptor in humans. A problem or absence with this receptor could alter the ability of one to have adequate sleep without medication. The sociocultural implication of this study is that if the phenotype was inherited, this could regulate sleep, and an alteration of the receptor would naturally disturb sleep for an individual. This would negatively impact aspects of life such as school, career, and every day events that involve monotonous tasks and focus.

This paper covers three areas of Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, a brief definition of the disorder is provided. Next, diagnosis is explained, with common characteristics, or “red flags”. Finally, the paper concludes with ways that a teacher in a mainstreamed classroom environment can assist a student with CAPD.

	Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) “refers to the efficiency and effectiveness by which the central nervous system (CNS) utilizes auditory information. Narrowly defined, (C)AP refers to the perceptual processing of auditory information in the CNS and the neurobiologic activity that underlies that processing and gives rise to electrophysiologic auditory potentials” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005), meaning it is a disorder wherein the central nervous system (i.e. the brain) cannot properly process things that are heard. People with CAPD can hear normally, and are therefore not considered “hearing impaired”; rather, the area of the brain that translates what we hear, separating words or differentiating conversation from background noise does not function as it typically should. 

	The earliest mention of the disorder that became CAPD is from the mid-1950s, called “auditory imperception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005) when researchers were evaluating children with communicative disorders. The Italian research team of Bocca, Calearo, and Cassinari began developing tests for these children in 1954; in 1961, Kimura “introduced dichotic testing and formulated a model to explain the physiology of the CANS underlying dichotic perception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). A national conference was held in 1977 that stimulated research on children with CAPD. 

	CAPD manifests itself in multiple ways: the person suffering may not be able to localize or hear sound in space; may have difficulty discriminating between two or more “acoustic events” (sound occurrences); may not be able to recognize sound patterns; may not be able to differentiate changes in speech (like detecting sarcasm based on change of voice); one sound may be blocked by a subsequent sound; may not have the ability to synthesize sound clues (that is, interpret in a meaningful way that they can then act upon); and may not be able to determine the sequence in which auditory information is presented (Ferre).

	In order to diagnose CAPD, the patient must be screened with “systematic observation of listening behavior and/or performance on tests of auditory function”, which may be conducted by “audiologists, SLPs, psychologists, and others using a variety of measures that evaluate auditory-related skills” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). This may include questionnaires and surveys, observation of auditory behaviors, including how the patient responds to certain stimuli. There is, at this time, no one tool or test that is used consistently to a high rate of diagnostic success, and there is no known cause for the disorder. Many tests used present the patient with multiple, simultaneous auditory stimuli and then ask for them to differentiate certain items, like a series of words or numbers. More advanced tests include recording acoustic signals within the ear and measuring the responses to the signals.

The play Twelfth Night seems to say that although disguise is in fact useful in perpetrating long bouts of deception, in the end a person must reject that newly formed guise, or else risk losing themselves forever in the process. A big problem with ending a deception, however, is that one may find themselves alienated in the process. Therefore, in the end, one must decide between one’s own self preservation, or the preservation of relationships with those around them. For although some will respond neutrally to discovering that they’ve been tricked, still others will not take the deception so lightly, and will be likely be offended by the whole charade.
The topic of deception in gender role reversal is especially problematic, because it brings up many side issues, perhaps the most important one being, why? Why does the subject feel the need to shirk their own identity and take up a disguise in the form of the opposite gender? In Viola’s case, it is obviously a form of self protection.: “I’ll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)
Having newly arrived in a foreign land, Viola feels it necessary to pretend to be a man to protect herself from would be attackers. Viola’s plan works, but it also alienates her from the women around her, cutting her off from an important support system. To make matters worse, she is apparently so convincing at appearing to be a man that Olivia confuses her with Sebastian, and in effect falls in love with her. “Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.” (5.1.138) On top of that, she also has to deal with suppressed romantic desires between her and Orsino: “Boy, thou hast said to me a thousand times/ Thou never shouldst love woman like to me.” (5.1. 260-261)
Although this may be a somewhat progressive attitude, to the modern reader, Twelfth Night may be seen as an illustration of how deception may help facilitate the unveiling of suppressed emotions, especially in the cases of Olivia and Orsino.
